Description:  This example creates a LAMMPS-formatted polycrystalline data and dump files using the nanocrystal_builder.py and combat.py modules.

Prerequisites:  NumPy, SciPy, nanocrystal_builder.py, combat.py

Input files:  Requires a dump file (dump.singlecrystal) containing the crystal structure

Usage:  python nanocrystal_builder.py
	python addMoleculeID.py

Output:  Creates a data file called data.polycrystal that contains the atomic coordinates 
	 of a 100x100x100 Angstrom^3 polycrystalline sample.

Contributing Author:  Michael Fortunato and James Larentzos

Notes:  See Example A1 and A2 in the appendix of ARL Technical Report ARL-TR-8213, 2017.
	Example A1 generates the dump file and Example A2 generates the polycrystal data file in molecular format.

References:

1. Fortunato, M.E.; Mattson, J.; Taylor, D.E.; Larentzos, J.P.; Brennan, J.K.  
   "Pre- and Post-Processing Tools to Create and Characterize Particle-Based Composite Model Structures", 
   ARL Technical Report, ARL-TR-8213, 2017.